body.name: The Doctor's Secret: An Unputdownable Gripping Psychological Thriller With A Killer Twist
body.description: She thought she loved an innocent man. She was wrong.City coroner Doctor Stacy Lewis just learned that her fiance, Doctor Henry Goldberg, is the prime suspect in a serial murder case.She can’t believe for a moment that the man she loves and trusts more than anything is responsible for killing three women.But one man is convinced. And that’s her ex-boyfriend and the detective on the case, Matt Ensor.Her coworker at the city hospital, the charming ER doctor Henry, swept in quickly to steal her away--something that Matt has never forgiven.Stacy is convinced that Matt’s judgment is skewed by his hatred of Henry and desire to get Stacy back. She is willing to do anything to clear his name--even abuse her position as city coroner.Determined to convince Matt that he’s got the wrong man, she goes ahead with her plan and gets Henry out on bail.But then women start disappearing again.She has to figure out how to get herself out of this situation. Before it’s too late.The Doctor's Secret – the gripping psychological thriller perfect for fans of Freida McFadden, Daniel Hurst, and K L Slater.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Pretty good book but main character was too much of an irritating female who lacked common sense. I still gave it a five due to well written story and will definitely read another book by Cole Baxter

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It was a good read. With a doctor with more issues than the murderer. But check it out and see if you agree with me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good in the beginning....
reviews.reviewText: This book was good in the beginning and the end. However, the middle of the book dragged on and on...and was repetitive at timesStacey is a coroner who is engaged to Henry...a Dr. At first they seem happy, but as time goes on Henry seems to have issues with intimacy and his mood swings. Stacey is always trying to make things right (ugghh)Then there is murders of young women who look a lot like stacey! Stacey's Ex, Matt is a detective and is on this case. He doesn't like Henry and it seems lke Henry is #!1 suspect. Stacey wants to prove her fiance's innocent but things aren't adding up.The investigation part is where things went slowly. There was no real twist and I saw what the ending was from the middle of this book I felt this book could've been done in 300 pages not 400. I still recommend itI

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What a debut
reviews.reviewText: This book was written up to Cole Baxter"s high standards. This was well written and the suspense was nail biting and heart thumping. I was surpirised at the ending. I do not want to spoil this book for others. Enjoy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars REALLY BAD BOOK
reviews.reviewText: First of all this book should have been about half the length. It just went on and on. Honestly the main character was unbelievable. No-one is that stupid. And she just kept getting dummer as the story went on. Totally unrealistic. I normally pass all my books on, but this is going right in the trash.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Too many errors
reviews.reviewText: I am a copyeditor, so when I read for pleasure, I don't expect to have to work. There were too many punctuation errors, typos, wrong words, and run-on sentences/comma splices. I gave up after a few chapters. This could have been a decent book otherwise.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars The Doctor’s Secret
reviews.reviewText: This was a very enjoyable psychological thriller. Lots of mystery and suspense. There are a lot of twists and turns that kept me on the edge of my seat. The plot is so well developed and compelling. This is a must-read.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Ohmigod…another spectacular read from Cole Baxter.
reviews.reviewText: Cole Baxter definitely knows how to scare the bejeezus out of his audience. This one is crazy good—and scary! Oh man…the storyline is so psychologically compelling; the characters are somewhat twisted; the plot is full of crazy twists and turns; and the ending gives you resolution—yet still makes you question what you’ve read. This one deserves more than 5 stars in my opinion! If you like psychological stories with a touch of romance—grab this book today. (I voluntarily reviewed an advance reader copy of this book and was totally blown away by it!) ❤️❤️❤️
